'''Catholic Schools Board Limited''' is a private company, originally established by the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Wellington|Archdiocese of Wellington]]. It was established when [[Wellington]] Catholic schools began [[State-integrated school|integrating into the state system]]. The Catholic Schools Board Limited manages school property and attendance dues. Attendance dues are a legal obligation of enrolment in Catholic schools and are not a donation or tax deductible.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.csbl.co.nz/attendance-dues|title=Attendance Dues|work=csbl.co.nz|accessdate=29 March 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402133050/http://www.csbl.co.nz/attendance-dues|archivedate=2 April 2015|df=}}</ref> The Palmerston North Diocese schools are now also managed by Catholic Schools Board Limited.

The Catholic Religious Order or Diocese who own each school add to funding received by the Catholic Schools Board Limited.

