'''InsideTrack''' supports colleges and universities in increasing student enrollment, persistence, and graduation rates.  The company was founded in 2001 by [[Alan Tripp]], who also founded [[SCORE! Educational Centers]], and is based in [[San Francisco, California]], with additional operations in [[Portland, Oregon]] and [[Nashville, Tennessee]].

They were named one of the 10 most innovative companies in education by [[Fast Company (magazine)]] in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fastcompany.com/most-innovative-companies/2013/industry/education |title=The World's Top 10 Most Innovative Companies in Education |publisher=http://www.fastcompany.com |date=2013-02-11 |accessdate=2013-02-11}}</ref>  Also in 2013, a study documenting the impact of their work, conducted by professor [[Eric Bettinger]] of the [[Stanford Graduate School of Education]] and [[Rachel Baker]] of [[University of California Irvine]] was published by the [[American Educational Research Association]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aera.net/Newsroom/AERAPublishedResearchofNote/TheEffectsofStudentCoaching/tabid/15219/Default.aspx |title=The Effects of Student Coaching  |publisher=http://www.aera.net |date=2013-10-10 |accessdate=2013-10-10}}</ref>

The company provides coaching programs, [[analytics]], [[technology]] and [[management consulting]] services to many [[types of educational institutions]] including public and private universities, community colleges and distance education programs.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.insidehighered.com/news/2013/05/24/insidetracks-student-coaching-proves-completion-payoff |title=Coach Knows Best |publisher=insidehighered.com |date=2013-05-24 |accessdate=2013-05-24}}</ref>

