The '''Institute for Learning in Higher Education''' (LiHE) was set up in 2007 to advance [[Student-centred learning|learning centred]] [[higher education]]. It functions a network bringing together international researchers and practitioners within higher education, to further advance research in this area. LiHE is voluntarily run by a group of co-directors, all serving as professors at various universities and business schools.<ref>[http://lihe.info/about-lihe/ About LIHE] accessed 7 July 2012.</ref>

The executive director of LiHE is Professor Dr. Claus Nygaard ([[Copenhagen Business School]], [[Denmark]]). Co-directors are Professor Dr. John Branch (University of Michigan, Ann Arbor); Professor Dr. Paul Bartholomew (Aston University, Birmingham). Previous co-directors are Dr. Nigel Courtney ([[Cass Business School]], [[London]] ); Professor Clive Holtham ([[Cass Business School]], [[London]] ).<ref>[http://lihe.info/about-lihe/ About LIHE] accessed 7 July 2012.</ref>

