{{Infobox University |name = University of Economics in Bratislava |native_name = Ekonomická univerzita v Bratislave |established = 1940 |image_name = Ekonomicka univerzita.jpg |rector = Dr. h. c. prof. Ing. Rudolf Sivák,. PhD. |city = [[Bratislava]] |country = [[Slovak Republic]] |type = [[Public university|Public]] |students = 14,000 |staff = |faculty = |affiliations = [[Erasmus programme|ERASMUS]] |website = [http://www.euba.sk www.euba.sk] |address = Dolnozemská 1, 852 35 Bratislava 5, Slovak Republic, Europe |telephone = +421 2 67295 111 |nickname = EU }} {{unref|date=October 2018}} '''University of Economics in Bratislava''' ({{lang-sk|Ekonomická univerzita v Bratislave}}) is the oldest university of economics in [[Slovakia]].
==History==
The university was established in 1940 as a private university under the name '''Vysoká obchodná škola v Bratislave''' (College of Commerce in Bratislava), because of the situation in German-occupied [[Protectorate of Bohemia and Moravia]] where college and universities were closed down, where also many Slovak students were studying. It was nationalized in 1945 and renamed to ''Slovenská vysoká škola obchodná'' (Slovak College of Commerce). It was renamed again in 1949 to ''Vysoká škola hospodárskych vied'' (College of Business / Economic Sciences) and once again in 1952 to ''Vysoká škola ekonomická'' (College of Economics). The current name is used since 1992.
==Structure==
* Faculty of National Economy * Faculty of Commerce * Faculty of Business Informatics * Faculty of Management * Faculty of International Relations * Faculty of Applied Languages * Faculty of Business Administration in [[Košice]]
