{{Multiple issues| {{Notability|date=October 2014}} {{Refimprove|date=October 2014}} }} '''Western Upper Nile University''' is a proposed university in [[South Sudan]].
==Location== The [[public university]], when established, will maintain its main campus in the town of [[Bentiu]], in ''Rubkona County'', [[Unity State]], in northern [[South Sudan]], close to the International border with the [[Republic of Sudan]].<ref>[http://www.ovguide.com/bentiu-9202a8c04000641f8000000000e04beb# Western Upper Nile University Located In Bentiu]</ref>
==Overview== When established, the university will be the seventh (7th) public university in South Sudan.
